habitat_description: The Blanco blind salamander is originally described from a single specimen from 1951 as workers were drilling a hole for water in the bed of the Blanco River east of San Marcos in Hays County Texas (see Lannoo 2005 on authorship). Little information is available on habitat and egg deposition sites other than being subterranean and aquatic (Green et al. 2013).
